          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2021-07-15T15:01:23Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text>
            <![CDATA[ <p><strong>Federal Acquisition and Contracting Transparency Act of 2021 or FACT Act</strong></p> <p>This bill requires the Federal Acquisition Regulatory Council to amend the Federal Acquisition Regulation to require that a contractor, as a condition for being awarded a contract for the procurement of goods or services, disclose recent or current contracts or commercial ties with certain Chinese entities.</p> <p>The General Services Administration must establish and maintain a public database containing information about disclosed contracts. </p>]]>
          </text>
          <updateDate>2021-03-25T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
        </item>
